Steve,

You can use an &#39;OutletRes1D&#39; object instead of &#39;Outlet1D&#39;.  (At least, 
you can do this if you are working in C++.) This type of outlet 
simulates a boundary condition imposed by a fast crossflow across a 
flow straightener at the outlet. Both the temperature and mass 
fractions are held to values that you can set.

In the released version of Cantera, however, this object type is not 
accessible from MATLAB or Python.  But I have just now added the 
necessary hooks for MATLAB, and have run an example unstrained 
diffusion flame in MATLAB to verify that it works.  These capabilities 
will be present in the new release that I am trying to get out in the 
next few days.

Dave


